> Political Obama apologizes to aid group for US attack on Afghan clinic White House press secretary Josh Earnest arrives for the daily briefing at the White House in Washington, Wednesday, Oct. 7, 2015. Earnest made a statement about the U.S. airstrike that destroyed a hospital run by Doctors Without Borders on Saturday in Afghanistan and answered questions on the airstrike and President Barack Obama's telephone call with Afghanistan President Ashraf Ghani. (AP Photo/Susan Walsh) 
